Here's a precise prompt you can give to an AI agent:

---

> **Task:** Implement a **pin/unpin terminal window** UI component with auto hide/show behavior.
>
> ---
>
> ## 🧩 Component Behavior
>
> **Layout:**
>
> - The terminal window sits at the **bottom of the screen**.
> - When **unpinned**, the terminal **slides down and hides** below the viewport, leaving only a **thin placeholder bar** visible at the bottom edge.
> - The placeholder bar contains a **pin handler** (a thumbtack icon or drag handle) centered or aligned within it.
>
> ---
>
> **Unpinned State (Auto Hide):**
>
> - On unpin, the terminal **animates downward** (CSS `transform: translateY(100%)` or equivalent) until only the placeholder bar peeks out.
> - The placeholder bar remains **always visible** at the bottom so the user can interact with it.
> - The terminal is **not destroyed** — it stays mounted in the DOM, just visually hidden below the fold.
>
> ---
>
> **Auto Show on Hover:**
>
> - When the user **hovers over the placeholder bar / pin handler**, the terminal **slides back up** into view (animate `translateY(0)`).
> - Apply a **short hover delay** (~150–200ms) before triggering the show, to avoid accidental flickers.
> - The terminal stays visible **as long as the cursor is inside** the terminal panel or the placeholder bar.
> - When the cursor **leaves** the terminal area, it **slides back down** to hide again after a short delay (~300ms).
>
> ---
>
> **Pinned State (Locked):**
>
> - Clicking the **pin icon** toggles the pinned state.
> - When **pinned**, the terminal is **fully visible and locked** in place — hover events have no effect.
> - The main workspace **shrinks** (or adjusts its bottom padding/height) to accommodate the terminal so they don't overlap.
> - The pin icon visually changes state (e.g., rotated thumbtack, filled icon, or color change).
> - Clicking the pin icon again **unpins** the terminal and restores auto hide behavior.
>
> ---
>
> ### ⚙️ Technical Requirements
>
> - Use **CSS transitions** for smooth slide up/down animation (`transition: transform 0.25s ease`).
> - The terminal panel must have `position: fixed` at the bottom, with `z-index` high enough to float above content when unpinned.
> - The **placeholder bar** must always remain visible (never hidden), acting as the hover target and pin toggle host.
> - Manage state with a simple two-value toggle: `pinned | unpinned`.
> - Hover show/hide must use **debounced mouse enter/leave** events to prevent flickering.
> - When pinned, the layout container must respond by adjusting its **bottom offset** equal to the terminal height.
>
> ---
>
> ### 🎨 UX Details
>
> - Placeholder bar height: `~28–32px`
> - Terminal default height: `~250–300px`
> - Slide animation duration: `250ms`, easing: `ease` or `ease-in-out`
> - Hover delay before show: `150ms`
> - Hover delay before hide: `300ms`
> - Pin icon: thumbtack (📌) or a custom SVG, rotates `90deg` when pinned
> - Placeholder bar should have a subtle background (e.g., `#1e1e1e` or match terminal theme) with a centered drag/pin handle visible to invite interaction.
>
> ---
>
> ### ✅ Acceptance Criteria
>
> - [ ] Terminal hides below viewport on unpin with smooth animation
> - [ ] Placeholder bar always visible at bottom edge
> - [ ] Hovering placeholder bar restores terminal with animation
> - [ ] Mouse leave hides terminal again after delay
> - [ ] Pin locks terminal open and adjusts layout
> - [ ] Unpin restores auto hide behavior
> - [ ] No flicker on fast mouse movements (debounce applied)
> - [ ] Terminal content (shell/output) is preserved across hide/show cycles

